This is a weekly roundup of awesome DEV comments that you may have missed.  You are welcome and encouraged to boost posts and comments yourself using the **[#bestofdev](/t/bestofdev)** tag.

On the [Weekly Win post](https://dev.to/devteam/what-was-your-win-this-week-2k65), @gedalyakrycer is proud of gaining some more Gatsby knowledge and the start of their journey with DEV. We can't wait to see what you do next!

{% devcomment 1cbm9 %}

In the trials and tribulations of coding and IT, we all [live and learn] (https://dev.to/catalinmpit/6-things-i-learnt-after-programming-nearly-destroyed-my-life-4gkf), and that's been reflected in @shaijut's tips and tricks from their IT experiences. Thanks for the helpful information!
{% devcomment 1cbf2 %}

@raphael_jambalos offers some wisdom in the comments of a post about what it's like being a [self-taught developer.](https://dev.to/abdulbasit313/5-mistakes-i-wish-i-didn-t-make-as-a-self-taught-developer-gjk) It's awesome to see such helpful advice being shared across the DEV community.

{% devcomment 1ccjb %}


[Refactoring can be a pain.](https://dev.to/harshvats2000/please-refactor-your-code-1k3e) @dumazy shared some great tips to make the process as painless and simple as possible. Nice call on these!

{% devcomment 1cg5g %}


Thanks for sharing how you stay fit, @manpreet! Like @sarthology [said](https://dev.to/xenoxdev/how-do-you-stay-fit-these-days-37h3), it's so important to prioritize fitness as a developer. 

{% devcomment 1cfb3 %}




See you next week for more great comments ✌
